                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311020-128-off686 t18311020-128-crimeloc688"></join>. I was at his shop door on the evening of the 17th of October, about half-past six o'clock; I saw the prisoner in the act of taking the coat off the bar of the prosecutor's shop, which is next door to us - he went up Titchbourn-street; I pursued, and did not lose sight of him till he was taken - I brought him and the coat back.</p>
